<li>Locate one point <m>(x,y)</m> where the partial derivative <m>f_x(x,y)=
  0</m>.</li>
<li>Locate one point <m>(x,y)</m> where <m>f_x(x,y)\lt 0</m>.</li>
<li>Locate one point <m>(x,y)</m> where <m>f_y(x,y)>0</m>.</li>
<li>Suppose you have a different function <m>g</m>, and you know that <m>g(2,2) =
  4</m>, <m>g_x(2,2) > 0</m>, and <m>g_y(2,2) > 0</m>.  Using this information,
