<image source="images/fig_10_2_activity_grad.png" /> 
      \hspace{1in}
      <image source="images/fig_10_2_activity_grad.png" /> </figure>
</li>
<li>Suppose you have yet another function <m>h</m>, and you know that <m>h(2,2) =
  4</m>, <m>h_x(2,2) \lt  0</m>, and <m>h_y(2,2) > 0</m>.  Using this information,
  sketch a possible contour <m>h(x,y)=4</m> passing through
  <m>(2,2)</m> on the right side of <xref ref="F_10.2.activity.grad">Figure</xref>.
  Then include possible contours <m>h(x,y) = 3</m> and <m>h(x,y) = 5</m>.</li>
 </ol>  </statement>
