</me>
 
The number <m>I_H(94,75)</m> tells us that if the relative humidity increases by 1% from 75% while the temperature remains constant at <m>94^{\circ}</m>F, the heat index increases by approximately <m>0.9^{\circ}</m>F. In other words, it feels approximately <m>0.9^{\circ}</m>F warmer if the relative humidity increases by 1% from 75% while the temperature remains constant at <m>94^{\circ}</m>F, the heat index increases by approximately <m>0.9^{\circ}</m>F.</li>
